cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper deals with the application of machine learning algorithms for the detection of non-technical losses in large real-world datasets. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) since the detection of non-technical losses involves identifying fraudulent activities. The use of fuzzy logic and support vector machines also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and intelligent systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of imbalanced datasets, which is a common issue in data science and machine learning, and hence could also be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
